modules.description: This module decodes FIT record values using field-specific logic. It handles timestamps, scaled values with offset and factor, and coordinate decoding for latitude or longitude. Use it to convert raw FIT field values into their physical representations based on known encoding rules.

Handles decoding of fitness tracking records with optional numeric fields. Works with raw data messages to extract geographic, temporal, and biometric measurements. Useful for processing GPS and sensor data from wearable devices.

This module parses FIT binary files from fitness devices, handling headers and structured records with heterogeneous field values. It decodes raw data into physical values like timestamps, coordinates, and scaled measurements using predefined logic. Use it to extract GPS, biometric, and activity data from FIT files into usable formats like JSON or typed records.
